12/05/2010
PRISTINA, Kosovo -- Foreign Minister Skender Hyseni has asked Belgrade to provide facts about mass graves dating from the 1998-1999 conflict. "Serbia is responsible to make mass grave sites containing Albanian bodies public," Hyseni was quoted as saying on Tuesday (May 11th). The latest one, believed to contain the bodies of 250 Kosovo Albanians, was found in Raska, Serbia, near the Kosovo border. (Kohavision, TV 21, KLAN Kosova, RTK - 11/05/10)
